2. Core RH Alpha Coordinate
============================================================

Definition:

  ρ = β + iγ
  α(ρ) = Re(ρ) - 1/2 = β - 1/2

States:

  ridge:
    α = 0
    Re(ρ)=1/2
    candidate critical-line closure

  off_ridge:
    α ≠ 0
    Re(ρ)≠1/2
    possible off-ridge zero candidate
    must generate debt or contradiction

Debt approximation:

  D_perp(α;U)
    = 1/(2U) ∫_0^U [
        (exp(αu)-1)^2 + (exp(-αu)-1)^2
      ] du

Small-alpha approximation:

  D_perp(α;U) ≈ (U^2/3) α^2

Formal small theorem target:

  α≠0 and U≠0 ⇒ D_quad(α,U)>0

where:

  D_quad(α,U) = (U^2/3) α^2

Important:
  D_quad positivity is not RH.
  It only formalizes local normal-deviation debt.


