3. Corrected Off-Ridge Interpretation
============================================================

Incorrect off-ridge test:

  Pick arbitrary α≠0 and arbitrary t.
  Check ζ(1/2+α+it).

This is too weak, because almost all arbitrary points are not zeros.

Correct off-ridge object:

  off-ridge zero candidate:
    ζ(1/2+α+iγ)=0
    α≠0
    0<Re(s)<1

Finite-window closure test:

  N_total(T) = total zeros in critical strip up to height T
  N_line(T)  = zeros captured on critical line up to height T
  OffCount(T)=N_total(T)-N_line(T)

Finite-window off-ridge closure:

  OffCount(T)=0

Global RH target:

  ∀T, OffCount(T)=0

or equivalently:

  ¬∃ρ,
    ζ(ρ)=0
    0<Re(ρ)<1
    Re(ρ)≠1/2


============================================================
4. Zero Locator: From N_sm to θ Midpoint
============================================================

Smooth zero-counting approximation:

  N_sm(T) =
    T/(2π) log(T/(2π)) - T/(2π) + 7/8

Naive locator:

  solve N_sm(T)=n

Observed issue:
  This tends to place the guess near the step right-end,
  often producing a positive height bias.

Corrected locator:

  solve θ(T)/π = n - 3/2

Interpretation:
  The zero is closer to the middle of a counting jump,
  not the right edge of the continuous counting approximation.

Pipeline:

  Input:
    n

  Step 1:
    T0 = solve θ(T0)/π = n - 3/2

  Step 2:
    Δ = 2π / log(T0/(2π))

  Step 3:
    Search bracket:
      [T0 - 2Δ, T0 + 2Δ]

  Step 4:
    Use Hardy Z(t) to find sign change/root.

  Step 5:
    Refine root:
      bisection / secant / Newton

  Step 6:
    Verify ξ-symmetry:
      R(α,t)=|ξ(1/2+α+it)|^2

  Step 7:
    If doing finite-window verification:
      compare N_total and N_line.


============================================================
5. Hardy Z and ξ Symmetry
============================================================

Hardy Z:

  Z(t) = exp(i θ(t)) ζ(1/2 + it)

For real t:
  Z(t) is real.

Critical-line zeros:
  Z(γ_n)=0

Therefore:
  θ midpoint gives a near root.
  Hardy Z refinement locates the actual γ_n.

ξ symmetric residual:

  ξ(s) = 1/2 s(s-1) π^(-s/2) Γ(s/2) ζ(s)

Use:

  R(α,t) = |ξ(1/2 + α + it)|^2

For a critical-line zero:

  R(α,γ_n) ≈ A_n α^2 + B_n α^4 + ...
  centered single-well at α=0

For a hypothetical off-ridge pair:

  zeros at α=+α0 and α=-α0
  R(α,t) shows split double-well

Classification:

  centered_single_well:
    supports critical-line zero shape

  split_double_well_candidate:
    possible off-ridge pair pattern
    requires high-risk audit

  numerical_unstable:
    precision insufficient


